<div class="WordSection1">
<h3>How do I apply?</h3>
<p>An online application will be available shortly. Check with your <a href="http://www.byui.edu/online/pathway/locations"> local Pathway mission couple</a> for more information.</p>
<h3 class="MsoNoSpacing1"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #595959; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 166;"> </span>When should I apply?</h3>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing1"><span>New Pathway students are admitted into  any of the three BYU-Idaho Semesters (Winter, Spring, &amp; Fall). Applications deadlines for each semester may vary. Please check with your local mission couple for details.</span></p>
<h3 class="MsoNoSpacing1"><span>Do I need to take any special tests (e.g., ACT/SAT/TOEFL) prior to applying?</span></h3>
<p>Students are not required to take any standardized test for acceptance to the Academic Start level of the Pathway Program. However, all students must maintain a 'B' average to be considered for advancement into a degree program. Additionally, students whose native language is not English must take an English Proficiency assessment.</p>
<h3>What happens next?</h3>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing1">After your Pathway mission couple  submits your application you will receive an email from BYU-Idaho within two weeks letting you know if you have been accepted and what to do next.</p>
<h3 class="MsoNoSpacing1">Have questions?</h3>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing1">Contact the <a href="x28630.xml">Online Support Center</a> at (866) 672-2984 or email at <a href="mailto:onlinelearning@byui.edu"><span>onlinelearning@byui.edu</span></a></p>
<p class="MsoNoSpacing" style="color: #595959; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 16.0pt;"> </p>
